====Usage notes====
Even if it is translated as to [[be]], 是 is used only to link two nouns or nominal expression.
: {{zh-usex|我 '''是''' 老師|I '''am''' a teacher}}
: {{zh-usex|泰晤士河 是 ^英國 第二 長 的 河流。|The River Thames '''is''' the second longest river in the UK.}}
It can't be used to link a noun and an adjective. The following sentence is wrong : 
: 这是好。
The correct sentence is
: {{zh-usex|這 '''很''' 好|This '''is (very)''' good}}
Here [[很]] is used as a filler, to link a noun and an adjective and is not interpreted as very. Not using it would sound unnatural.
A way to use 是 with an adjective is to use {{zh-l|的}} after the adjective to turn it into a noun.
: {{zh-usex|那 只 猫 '''是''' 黑 的|This cat is black (This cat is a black one)}}

